  "body": "<!-- This form is for bug reports and feature requests ONLY! \r\n\r\nIf you're looking for help check [Stack Overflow](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/kubernetes) and the [troubleshooting guide](https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/debug-application-cluster/troubleshooting/).\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Is this a BUG REPORT or FEATURE REQUEST?**:\r\n\r\n/kind bug\r\n/sig node\r\n\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\nPrometheus metrics endpoint for PVC volume stats is showing stale data for volumes no longer mounted to node\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\nPrometheus metrics endpoint for PVC volume stats only shows metrics for currently mounted volumes.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**: Migrate a pod with a PVC/volume mount to a different node. Observe that the PVC volume metrics on the previous node still report the last known values.\r\n\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\nThe /stats/summary endpoint correctly reports only the currently mounted PVCs. It's only the /metrics endpoint that reports stale volume metrics\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`): 1.8.3\r\n- Cloud provider or hardware configuration: AWS\r\n- OS (e.g. from /etc/os-release): Debian GNU/Linux 8 (jessie)\r\n- Kernel (e.g. `uname -a`): 4.9.0-0.bpo.2-amd64 #1 SMP Debian 4.9.18-1~bpo8+1 (2017-04-10) x86_64\r\n- Install tools:\r\n- Others:\r\n",
